	* an equivalent amount of electricity to the electricity accounted for has been firmly nominated to the alloÂ­cated interconnection capacity by all responsible transÂ­mission system operators in the country of origin, the country of destination and, if relevant, each third counÂ­try of transit;
	* an equivalent amount of electricity to the electricity accounted for has been firmly registered in the schedule of balance by the responsible transmission system operaÂ­tor on the Community side of an interconnector; and
	* the nominated capacity and the production of electricity from renewable energy sources by the installation referred to in paragraph 2(b) refer to the same period of time;
	* the electricity is produced by a newly constructed installation that became operational after 25 June 2009 or by the increased capacity of an installation that was refurbished after that date, under a joint project as referred to in paragraph 1; and
	* the amount of electricity produced and exported has not received support from a support scheme of a third country other than investment aid granted to the installation.
	* construction of the interconnector started by 31 December 2016;
	* it is not possible for the interconnector to become operaÂ­tional by 31Â December 2020;
