In its reports, the Commission shall, in particular, analyse:
* the scope for identifying, in a scientifically objective manner, geographical areas of high biodiversity value that are not covÂ­ered in ArticleÂ 17(3);
* the impact of increased demand for biomass on biomass using sectors;
* the availability of biofuels made from waste, residues, non-food cellulosic material and ligno-cellulosic material; and
* indirect land-use changes in relation to all production pathways.
* the better use of structural funds and framework programmes;
* the better and increased use of funds from the European Investment Bank and other public finance institutions;
* better access to risk capital notably by analysing the feasibilÂ­ity of a risk sharing facility for investments in energy from renewable sources in the Community similar to the Global Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy Fund initiative which is aimed at third countries;
* the better coordination of Community and national funding and other forms of support; and
* the better coordination in support of renewable energy iniÂ­tiatives whose success depends on action by actors in several Member States.
